Follow docs/policy/lint-policy.md for the full lint architecture.

## Patterns the linter does not enforce (agent should follow)

**Max 3 parameters**: When a function needs more than 3 parameters, bundle extras into an options object. The linter flags excess params but does not suggest this fix.

```ts
// Prefer
function createUser(options: { name: string; email: string; role: string }): User { ... }

// Avoid (linter will error)
function createUser(name: string, email: string, role: string, avatar?: string): User { ... }
```

**Absolute imports**: Use the `#` path alias for workspace-internal imports. The linter blocks relative `./` imports but does not enforce which alias to use.

```ts
// Prefer
import { hexToRgb } from '#utils/color.utils.js';

// Avoid (linter will error)
import { hexToRgb } from '../utils/color.utils.js';
```

Run `pnpm nx lint <project>` to validate; the linter will flag any other violations (import type, explicit return types, type vs interface, null vs undefined, curly braces, etc.).
